/* War on terror */ per talk page

Suggestions for simplicity. Unless actual physical danger is involved, any professional position—whether governmental or civilian—is just that: a paid position. "Service" is often used arbitrarily and gratuitously, to glamorize positions associated with government policy. I don't believe that corresponds with WP's mission to present information objectively. (I also don't think a president who knowingly lead the US into a fraudulent war "served" it, either, but that's another matter.)

"in order to overthrow the Taliban, destroy al-Qaeda, and capture Osama bin Laden" implies Bush accomplished these things. Al-Qaeda still exists and the subsequent administration killed bin Laden in Pakistan, not Afghanistan. Not to mention the Taliban ultimately recaptured Afghanistan. "In an effort to" is more accurate, as it reflects the intention and the fact that there were mixed outcomes.
